  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The DUO study's main objective is to evaluate, in the real life, the prevalence of
      cardiovascular risk in patients with prostate cancer that hormone treatment of androgen
      suppression by Degarelix was introduced.

      This study will also assess, at the initiation of therapy, the prevalence of osteoporosis,
      metabolic comorbidities, depression, sexual and geriatric patients suffering from prostate
      cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
